OLD REVIEW: READ IT HOVEWER, IF YOU WANT MY OPINION ABOUT THIS GAME.

I'm very glad that this game has finally come, but there are bothersome issues in every movie (Opening included) for me: the music goes crazy and starts to rustle every 2 seconds, and this ruins every cut scene in my gameplay. Actually, for this reason the storymode is simply inaccesible for me. The strange thing is that, if I try to run the Movies "out of the game" and using VLC, selecting them directly from their folder, they work properly. (???). But when they are activated in-game, both the opening and all the Movies caw and leap up every 2 seconds. If someone could help me with this issue, I'd be very grateful.

Other points down: 
- the sound effects were far better in BBCSE. Here the developers have decreased the impact of punches and kicks, and of many special moves of various characters. (For example, all Jin Kisaragi ice attacks);
- there is no Score calculator during Arcade Mode, and the game doen't explain how you have earned the money you gain defeating enemies. Again, in BBCSE all of this stuff was done very well so I don't understand the reason why here it is so vague.

Coming to the positive things, we have:
+ new mechanics (the Overdrive is the GREATEST idea here);
+ new characters (and many of them - like Amane & Celica - are really WONDERFUL);
+ excellent variety (and quality) about environments.

For now, although I'm really displeased telling this, I cannot fully promote this game. :-( For me, it is "Movie broken" and with half of the contents not enjoyable.

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SUPPLEMENT TO THE OLD REVIEW

OK: after 170 hours of gameplay, I have to admit that, overall, this game is really GREAT! 

Here are the reasons for my change of opinion:
+++ all the new Charcaters are very funny and well differentiated;
+++ Abyss Mode is really amazing, far better then in the previous Chapter, because here you have 10 independent paths to complete (the same for every Character, but each Character has its personal results) and when you buy an item it is forever (while on Continuum Shift you have to buy it everytime you want to use it);
+++ I enjoyed very much the main Campaign, although I was forced everytime there was a Movie to exit the game and play it manually from the Game Folder (my damned "cinematics issue" isn't still solved);
+++ I'm glad that the next Blazblue Game will be the last, and end this wonderful Saga, because when someone makes infinite a series there is often a drastic fall of quality and the series itself ends to be spoiled. VERY IMPORTANT: please, create a good ending! Don't ruin this Saga with a  precipitant and approximate finish.
